commentBody: Impeachment in the House is as inevitable as acquittal in the Senate. The process will change no one's mind & voters will vote regardless of the outcome. What we might get is a public demonstration of where the Democrats & Republicans stand on the rule of law. And with senators like Kennedy parroting Russian propaganda, it doesn't look good for Republicans. Everything I've read says in private the Republicans in both houses would love to see Trump's removal. This is their chance to acquit themselves in the eyes of the country & history.
